Mohale says his priorities include being explicit about what the organisation means by the term inclusive growth and to be a trusted adviser to the government. JOHANNESBURG - Business Leadership South Africa has announced that its new CEO will be Bonang Mohale who was previously the organisation's deputy chair.The organisation has been heavily involved in conversations with the government after the ratings downgrade and the Cabinet reshuffle.Mohale says his priorities include being explicit about what the organisation means by the term inclusive growth and to be a trusted adviser to government.He also says they want to help protect the law of the land. We really want to stand for the protection of our Constitution, including all the Chapter 9 institutions, but in particular the office of the Public Protector because we know that s the one that was under the most severe attacks. (Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)